In a bid to accelerate digital financial payments and foster customer loyalty, Tigo has awarded 2m/- each to the first 20 winners of the ongoing promotion campaign. The winners were drawn from a pool of Tigo Pesa customers who conducted different transactions such as Lipa Kwa Simu, Bill Payments, Government Payments, On-net peer transactions and receiving money from another mobile network. Tigo Pesa High Value Customers Segment Manager, Mary Rutta said, “The heartbeat of Tanzania’s economy is in digital payments. This demographic is inclined to technology and at Tigo, we are always coming up with innovative products and services. Through this promotion, we want to lead the transformation to a cashless society. We are excited with how Tigo Pesa customers have jumped on this promotion we look forward to awarding cash prizes of over 325m/- in the next five weeks.” “This transact and win promotion is exclusively for Tigo Pesa customers, where we will have a total of 111 winners, 20 winners winning 2m/- every week for 5 weeks, 10 winners to get the grand prize of 10m/- end of the promotion and 1 overall winner getting 25m/-,” she said.